📊 Framework Multidimensional de Incertidumbre Económica¶

Risk Index - Crisis Tracker v2¶

🎯 Descripción General¶

Este notebook implementa un framework multidimensional para la cuantificacin de incertidumbre econmica basado en la investigacin acadmica desarrollada en los papers:

  • "A Multidimensional Framework for Economic Uncertainty Quantification"
  • "Fiscal Policy Errors Under Economic Uncertainty: A DSGE Model with Imperfect Information and Learning"

El framework va ms all de los ndices tradicionales de incertidumbre al capturar mltiples dimensiones de ambigedad predictiva, proporcionando una visin ms completa y matizada del riesgo econmico.

🔬 Marco Teórico¶

La incertidumbre econmica se descompone en tres dimensiones fundamentales:

1. Model Dispersion (Dispersión entre Modelos)¶

  • Captura el desacuerdo entre diferentes metodologas de forecasting
  • Mide la incertidumbre estructural sobre el modelo econmico apropiado
  • Identifica perodos donde distintos marcos analticos proporcionan recomendaciones conflictivas

2. Within-Model Variability (Variabilidad Intra-Modelo)¶

  • Mide el rango de resultados plausibles dentro de un marco de modelado especfico
  • Corresponde a la incertidumbre paramtrica y volatilidad estocstica
  • Captura la volatilidad impredecible de las series econmicas

3. Temporal Instability (Inestabilidad Temporal)¶

  • Refleja cambios en las predicciones conforme nueva informacin est disponible
  • Indica incertidumbre sobre la persistencia de relaciones econmicas
  • Mide la revisin sustancial de forecasts a lo largo del tiempo

🛠️ Arquitectura del Sistema¶

El notebook est estructurado en mdulos funcionalmente cohesivos:

 Risk Index Framework

🤖 Modelos Implementados¶

1. Vector Autoregression (VAR)¶

  • Propsito: Modelo economtrico tradicional para anlisis multivariado
  • Fortalezas: Captura relaciones dinmicas entre variables econmicas
  • Uso: Generacin de intervalos de confianza (within-model uncertainty)

2. Random Forest¶

  • Propsito: Modelo de machine learning para capturar no-linealidades
  • Fortalezas: Robusto ante outliers y cambios estructurales
  • Uso: Modelo alternativo para dispersin entre modelos

3. ARIMA (AutoRegressive Integrated Moving Average)¶

  • Propsito: Modelo univariado clsico de series temporales
  • Fortalezas: Simplicidad y transparencia interpretativa
  • Uso: Tercer modelo para completar la dispersin multidimensional

📊 Metodología de Evaluación¶

Rolling Window Analysis¶

  • Evaluacin dinmica desde 2019Q1 hasta 2025Q1
  • Forecasting out-of-sample con ventana mvil
  • Mtricas de performance: MAE, RMSE, intervalos de confianza

Crisis Resilience Framework¶

  • Anlisis pre/post-COVID para medir adaptabilidad de modelos
  • Resilience Score = 1 / (Post-COVID MAE / Pre-COVID MAE)
  • Clasificacin: Modelos resilientes vs. modelos con "trauma estructural"

📥 Módulo de Carga y Procesamiento de Datos¶

Este mdulo constituye la base fundamental del framework de incertidumbre econmica, encargndose de la importacin, transformacin y preparacin de las series temporales econmicas que alimentan los modelos de forecasting.

🎯 Objetivos del Módulo¶

  • Carga automatizada de datos econmicos desde archivos Excel vintage
  • Transformaciones estadsticas (logaritmos, desestacionalizacin, diferenciacin)
  • Normalizacin de series temporales para anlisis economtrico
  • Gestin de vintages para anlisis histrico y evaluacin out-of-sample

🔄 Pipeline de Transformaciones¶

El sistema aplica una secuencia robusta de transformaciones a cada serie temporal:

1. Transformación Logarítmica¶

if log[i] == 1:
    dta[name] = np.log(dta[name])
  • Propsito: Estabilizar varianza y linearizar tendencias exponenciales
  • Aplicacin: Series con crecimiento compuesto (PIB, precios, salarios)

2. Desestacionalización (X-13 ARIMA-SEATS)¶

if detrend[i] == 1:
    resultst = x13_arima_analysis(endog=ser, prefer_x13=True, outlier=True)
    dta[name] = resultst.seasadj
  • Mtodo: X-13 ARIMA-SEATS (estndar del U.S. Census Bureau)
  • Beneficio: Elimina patrones estacionales para anlisis de ciclo econmico
  • Configuracin: Deteccin automtica de outliers habilitada

3. Diferenciación¶

if difer[i] != 0:
    dta[name] = dta[name].diff(difer[i]) * 100
  • Propsito: Convertir niveles a tasas de crecimiento
  • Escalado: Multiplicacin por 100 para expresar en porcentajes
  • Flexibilidad: Diferenciacin de orden variable segn caractersticas de la serie

4. Desplazamiento Temporal¶

if cross[i] != 0:
    dta[name] = dta[name].shift(cross[i])
  • Aplicacin: Ajuste de timing para indicadores adelantados/retrasados
  • Uso: Sincronizacin de series con diferentes lags informativos

📊 Gestión de Datos Vintage¶

El sistema implementa una arquitectura vintage que preserva el contexto histrico:

  • Vintage Dating: Cada dataset refleja la informacin disponible en una fecha especfica
  • Real-time Analysis: Permite evaluacin de modelos en condiciones realistas
  • Historical Consistency: Mantiene trazabilidad de revisiones de datos

🗂️ Estructura de Datos¶

Datos Mensuales¶

  • Frecuencia: Mensual (M)
  • Scope: Indicadores de alta frecuencia (produccin industrial, empleo, PMI)
  • Transformacin: Aplicacin completa del pipeline segn configuracin

Datos Trimestrales¶

  • Frecuencia: Trimestral (Q)
  • Scope: Cuentas nacionales y agregados macroeconmicos
  • Intervencin COVID: Incorporacin de variables dummy para perodo pandmico

⚙️ Configuración Paramétrica¶

El sistema utiliza archivos de configuracin que especifican las transformaciones:

series_m = pd.read_excel(fichero_mensual)    # Configuracin mensual
series_q = pd.read_excel(fichero_trimestral) # Configuracin trimestral

Parmetros por serie:

  • logs: Aplicar transformacin logartmica (0/1)
  • detrend: Aplicar desestacionalizacin (0/1)
  • difer: Orden de diferenciacin (0, 1, 2...)
  • cross: Desplazamiento temporal (+/- perodos)

import os

from statsmodels.tsa.x13 import x13_arima_analysis

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Transormacin
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

def transformacion(df, log, detrend, difer, cross):  # cambiar intgr por detrend
    dta = df.copy()
    
    for i, (name, column) in enumerate(dta.items()):
        
        if log[i] == 1:
            dta[name] = np.log(dta[name])
            
        if detrend[i] == 1:  # cambiar intgr por detrend
            limit = dta[name].last_valid_index()
            ser = dta[name].dropna()
            resultst = x13_arima_analysis(
                endog=ser[:limit], 
                x12path=None, 
                prefer_x13=True, 
                trading=False, 
                outlier=True
            )
            dta.loc[:limit, name] = resultst.seasadj
            
        if difer[i] != 0:
            dta[name] = dta[name].diff(difer[i]) * 100
            
        if cross[i] != 0:
            dta[name] = dta[name].shift(cross[i])
            
    return dta


def process_file(file_path, freq):
        """Funcin auxiliar para procesar archivos Excel"""
        if not os.path.exists(file_path):
            raise FileNotFoundError(f"No se encuentra el archivo: {file_path}")
        df = pd.read_excel(file_path)
        df = df.rename(columns={'Unnamed: 0': 'Fecha'})
        df.index = pd.PeriodIndex(df.Fecha.tolist(), freq=freq)
        df.drop('Fecha', axis=1, inplace=True)
        return df.loc['20000101':]

def load_data(vintage, path, sub, series_m, series_q):
    x = str(vintage)
    print(f"Procesando vintage: {x}")

    # Procesar datos mensuales
    file_m = os.path.join(path, 'data', 'Vintage', 'monthly', sub, f'{x}_m_rev.xlsx')
    orig_m = process_file(file_m, 'M')
    
    # Normalizar caracteres especiales
    orig_m.columns = orig_m.columns.str.replace('[]', lambda m: {'':'A','':'E','':'I','':'O','':'U'}[m.group()], regex=True)
    
    dta_m = transformacion(orig_m, series_m['logs'], series_m['detrend'], series_m['difer'], series_m['cross'])
    dta_m.to_excel(os.path.join(path, 'data', 'Vintage', 'desest', f'{x}_m_dtrend.xlsx'))

    # Procesar datos trimestrales
    file_q = os.path.join(path, 'data', 'Vintage', 'quarterly', sub, f'{x}_q_rev.xlsx')
    orig_q = process_file(file_q, 'Q')
    orig_q.columns = orig_q.columns.str.replace('[]', lambda m: {'':'A','':'E','':'I','':'O','':'U'}[m.group()], regex=True)
    
    dta_q = transformacion(orig_q, series_q['logs'], series_q['detrend'], series_q['difer'], series_q['cross'])
    dta_q.to_excel(os.path.join(path, 'data', 'Vintage', 'desest', f'{x}_q_dtrend.xlsx'))

    # Cargar intervencin COVID
    interv_file = os.path.join(path, 'data', 'Vintage', 'quarterly', 'intervencin.xlsx')
    intervcovid = process_file(interv_file, 'Q')
    
    # Merge con datos de intervencin
    dta_q = pd.merge(dta_q, intervcovid, left_index=True, right_index=True, how='inner')
    dta_q['Intervencin'] = dta_q['Intervencin'].fillna(0)

    return types.SimpleNamespace(
        orig_m=orig_m,
        dta_m=dta_m,
        orig_q=orig_q,
        dta_q=dta_q,
        intervcovid=intervcovid
    )

🤖 Módulo de Modelado VAR (Vector Autoregression)¶

Este mdulo implementa el primer pilar del framework multidimensional de incertidumbre, desarrollando modelos Vector Autoregression (VAR) para la prediccin del PIB y la generacin de intervalos de confianza que capturan la within-model variability.

🎯 Objetivos del Módulo¶

  • Construccin automtica de modelos VAR multivariados para forecasting del PIB
  • Seleccin inteligente de predictores basada en correlaciones empricas
  • Estimacin robusta con seleccin automtica de lags ptimos
  • Generacin de predicciones con intervalos de confianza para anlisis de incertidumbre

📊 Metodología VAR¶

¿Qué es un modelo VAR?¶

El Vector Autoregression es un modelo economtrico que captura las interdependencias dinmicas entre mltiples series temporales:

Y_t = c + AY_{t-1} + AY_{t-2} + ... + AY_{t-p} + _t

Donde:

  • Y_t: Vector de variables endgenas (PIB + predictores)
  • A: Matrices de coeficientes autorregresivos
  • p: Nmero de lags ptimos
  • _t: Vector de errores con estructura de covarianza

⚙️ Estimación del Modelo VAR¶

Selección Automática de Lags¶

  • Criterio AIC: Akaike Information Criterion para balance parsimonia-ajuste
  • Rango flexible: Evaluacin hasta 4 lags (un ao de historia trimestral)

🚀 Integración con Framework de Incertidumbre¶

Este mdulo VAR constituye la base economtrica para:

  1. Within-Model Variability: Los intervalos de confianza del VAR capturan la incertidumbre paramtrica
  2. Model Dispersion: Las predicciones VAR se comparan con Random Forest y ARIMA
  3. Temporal Instability: El modelo se re-estima en ventanas rolling para capturar inestabilidad
  4. Resilience Analysis: Performance pre/post-COVID mide adaptabilidad estructural

Nota Metodolgica: El VAR representa el gold standard economtrico para modelado multivariado de series temporales, proporcionando tanto predicciones puntuales como medidas de incertidumbre fundamentales para el anlisis de riesgo macroeconmico.

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from statsmodels.tsa.api import VAR

def trimestralize_monthly_fixed(monthly_data):
    """Convierte datos mensuales a trimestrales con PeriodIndex"""
    # Convertir a timestamp si es necesario
    if isinstance(monthly_data.index, pd.PeriodIndex):
        monthly_data = monthly_data.copy()
        monthly_data.index = monthly_data.index.to_timestamp()
    
    # Resample to quarterly
    quarterly = monthly_data.resample('Q').last()
    
    # Convertir a PeriodIndex para que coincida con trimestrales
    quarterly.index = quarterly.index.to_period('Q')
    
    return quarterly

def find_gdp_column(quarterly_data):
    """Encuentra la columna del PIB"""
    gdp_candidates = [col for col in quarterly_data.columns if 'PRODUCTO' in col.upper()]
    if gdp_candidates:
        return gdp_candidates[0]
    else:
        print("Columnas disponibles:")
        for col in quarterly_data.columns[:10]:
            print(f"  {col}")
        return None

def prepare_var_data(mensuales, trimestrales, end_date='2024Q4'):
    """Versin arreglada"""
    print("Preparando datos para VAR (versin corregida)...")
    
    # 1. Trimestrializar mensuales CON PeriodIndex
    monthly_quarterly = trimestralize_monthly_fixed(mensuales)
    print(f"Monthly quarterly index type: {type(monthly_quarterly.index)}")
    print(f"Monthly quarterly index: {monthly_quarterly.index[0]} a {monthly_quarterly.index[-1]}")
    
    # 2. Encontrar PIB
    gdp_col = find_gdp_column(trimestrales)
    if gdp_col is None:
        return None, None
    
    # 3. Combinar con ndices compatibles
    gdp_data = trimestrales[[gdp_col]]
    print(monthly_quarterly.shape)
    selected_monthly = monthly_quarterly.iloc[:, :15]
    
    print(f"GDP index type: {type(gdp_data.index)}")
    print(f"Monthly index type: {type(selected_monthly.index)}")
    
    # Ahora deberan ser compatibles
    combined_data = pd.concat([gdp_data, selected_monthly], axis=1)
    print(f"Combined shape: {combined_data.shape}")
    
    # 4. Filtrar hasta 2024Q4
    end_period = pd.Period(end_date, freq='Q')
    combined_data = combined_data.loc[:end_period]
    
    # 5. Eliminar NaNs
    print(f"Antes de dropna: {combined_data.shape}")
    print(f"NaNs por columna: {combined_data.isna().sum()}")
    
    combined_data = combined_data.dropna()
    print(f"Despus de dropna: {combined_data.shape}")
    
    if len(combined_data) > 0:
        print(f"Datos finales:")
        print(f"Variables: {list(combined_data.columns)}")
        print(f"Perodo: {combined_data.index[0]} a {combined_data.index[-1]}")
        print(f"Observaciones: {len(combined_data)}")
        
        return combined_data, gdp_col
    else:
        print(" No quedan datos despus de limpiar")
        return None, None

def estimate_simple_var(data, gdp_col):
    """Estima VAR simple"""
    print(f"\nEstimando VAR...")
    
    # Crear modelo VAR
    model = VAR(data)
    
    # Seleccionar lags
    lag_order = model.select_order(maxlags=4)
    optimal_lags = lag_order.aic
    print(f"Lags ptimos (AIC): {optimal_lags}")
    
    # Estimar
    var_fitted = model.fit(optimal_lags)
    
    print(f"VAR estimado con {optimal_lags} lags")
    print(f"Variables: {var_fitted.names}")
    
    return var_fitted
def select_best_predictors(mensuales, trimestrales, n_vars=6):
    """Selecciona las n variables con mayor correlacin con PIB"""
    
    # 1. Trimestrializar mensuales
    monthly_quarterly = trimestralize_monthly_fixed(mensuales)
    
    # 2. Encontrar PIB
    gdp_col = find_gdp_column(trimestrales)
    if gdp_col is None:
        return None, None, None
    
    # 3. Obtener serie PIB
    gdp_series = trimestrales[gdp_col]
    
    # 4. Combinar TODAS las variables (mensuales + trimestrales sin PIB)
    # Trimestrales sin PIB
    other_quarterly = trimestrales.drop(columns=[gdp_col])
    
    # Combinar
    all_predictors = pd.concat([monthly_quarterly, other_quarterly], axis=1)
    
    print(f"Variables candidatas: {all_predictors.shape[1]}")
    print(f"Perodo comn: {all_predictors.index[0]} a {all_predictors.index[-1]}")
    
    # 5. Calcular correlaciones con PIB
    correlations = []
    
    for col in all_predictors.columns:
        # Datos comunes (sin NaNs)
        common_data = pd.concat([gdp_series, all_predictors[col]], axis=1).dropna()
        
        if len(common_data) > 10:  # Mnimo 10 observaciones
            corr = common_data.iloc[:, 0].corr(common_data.iloc[:, 1])
            correlations.append({
                'variable': col,
                'correlation': abs(corr),  # Valor absoluto
                'raw_correlation': corr,
                'n_obs': len(common_data)
            })
    
    # 6. Ordenar por correlacin
    correlations_df = pd.DataFrame(correlations).sort_values('correlation', ascending=False)
    
    print(f"\nTop 10 variables ms correlacionadas con PIB:")
    print("-" * 80)
    for i, row in correlations_df.head(10).iterrows():
        var_name = row['variable'][:50] + "..." if len(row['variable']) > 50 else row['variable']
        print(f"{row.name+1:2d}. {var_name:<53} | r={row['raw_correlation']:+.3f} | n={row['n_obs']:3d}")
    
    # 7. Seleccionar top n_vars
    selected_vars = correlations_df.head(n_vars)['variable'].tolist()
    
    # 8. Crear dataset final
    selected_data = all_predictors[selected_vars]
    final_data = pd.concat([gdp_series, selected_data], axis=1).dropna()
    
    print(f"\nVariables seleccionadas:")
    for i, var in enumerate([gdp_col] + selected_vars):
        var_short = var[:60] + "..." if len(var) > 60 else var
        print(f"{i+1}. {var_short}")
    
    print(f"\nDataset final:")
    print(f"Variables: {final_data.shape[1]} (PIB + {n_vars} predictores)")
    print(f"Observaciones: {final_data.shape[0]}")
    print(f"Perodo: {final_data.index[0]} a {final_data.index[-1]}")
    
    return final_data, gdp_col, correlations_df

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def rolling_var_evaluation(best_data, gdp_column, start_eval='2019Q1', end_eval='2025Q1'):
   """Evaluacin rolling del VAR"""
   
   # Convertir fechas a perodos
   start_period = pd.Period(start_eval, freq='Q')
   end_period = pd.Period(end_eval, freq='Q')
   
   # Crear lista de perodos a evaluar
   eval_periods = pd.period_range(start=start_period, end=end_period, freq='Q')
   
   results = []
   
   print(f"Evaluando VAR desde {start_eval} hasta {end_eval}")
   print("=" * 60)
   
   for i, target_period in enumerate(eval_periods):
       # Perodo de entrenamiento (hasta el trimestre anterior)
       train_end = target_period - 1
       
       print(f"\n{i+1}/{len(eval_periods)}: Prediciendo {target_period} usando datos hasta {train_end}")
       
       # Datos de entrenamiento
       train_data = best_data.loc[:train_end]
       
       # Verificar que hay suficientes datos
       if len(train_data) < 10:
           print(f"    Pocos datos de entrenamiento: {len(train_data)}")
           continue
       
       try:
           # Estimar VAR
           model = VAR(train_data)
           lag_order = model.select_order(maxlags=min(4, len(train_data)//10))
           optimal_lags = lag_order.aic
           var_fitted = model.fit(optimal_lags)
           
           # Forecast
           forecast = var_fitted.forecast(train_data.values, 1)
           gdp_forecast = forecast[0, 0]  # PIB es la primera columna
           
           # Valor real
           if target_period in best_data.index:
               gdp_real = best_data.loc[target_period, gdp_column]
               error = gdp_forecast - gdp_real
               
               results.append({
                   'period': target_period,
                   'forecast': gdp_forecast,
                   'actual': gdp_real,
                   'error': error,
                   'abs_error': abs(error),
                   'squared_error': error**2,
                   'train_obs': len(train_data),
                   'lags': optimal_lags
               })
               
               print(f"  Forecast: {gdp_forecast:.4f} | Real: {gdp_real:.4f} | Error: {error:+.4f}")
           else:
               print(f"    No hay dato real para {target_period}")
               
       except Exception as e:
           print(f"   Error: {str(e)}")
   
   if results:
       results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
       results_df.set_index('period', inplace=True)
       
       # Calcular mtricas
       mae = results_df['abs_error'].mean()
       rmse = np.sqrt(results_df['squared_error'].mean())
       
       print(f"\n" + "=" * 60)
       print(f"RESULTADOS FINALES:")
       print(f"Perodos evaluados: {len(results_df)}")
       print(f"Error Absoluto Medio (MAE): {mae:.4f}")
       print(f"Error Cuadrtico Medio (RMSE): {rmse:.4f}")
       
       return results_df, mae, rmse
   else:
       print(" No se obtuvieron resultados")
       return None, None, None

def plot_var_evaluation(results_df, gdp_column):
   """Grfico de evaluacin del VAR"""
   
   fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))
   
   # Grfico 1: Forecast vs Real
   ax1 = axes[0, 0]
   ax1.plot(results_df.index.to_timestamp(), results_df['forecast'], 'b-o', label='Forecast', markersize=4)
   ax1.plot(results_df.index.to_timestamp(), results_df['actual'], 'r-s', label='Real', markersize=4)
   ax1.set_title('VAR Forecast vs Real - PIB')
   ax1.set_ylabel('Valor')
   ax1.legend()
   ax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
   ax1.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   
   # Grfico 2: Errores
   ax2 = axes[0, 1]
   colors = ['red' if x < 0 else 'green' for x in results_df['error']]
   ax2.bar(results_df.index.to_timestamp(), results_df['error'], color=colors, alpha=0.7)
   ax2.axhline(y=0, color='black', linestyle='-', linewidth=0.8)
   ax2.set_title('Errores de Prediccin')
   ax2.set_ylabel('Error (Forecast - Real)')
   ax2.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
   ax2.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   
   # Grfico 3: Errores absolutos
   ax3 = axes[1, 0]
   ax3.plot(results_df.index.to_timestamp(), results_df['abs_error'], 'purple', marker='o', markersize=4)
   ax3.set_title('Errores Absolutos')
   ax3.set_ylabel('|Error|')
   ax3.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
   ax3.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   
   # Grfico 4: Distribucin de errores
   ax4 = axes[1, 1]
   ax4.hist(results_df['error'], bins=10, alpha=0.7, color='skyblue', edgecolor='black')
   ax4.axvline(x=0, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=2)
   ax4.set_title('Distribucin de Errores')
   ax4.set_xlabel('Error')
   ax4.set_ylabel('Frecuencia')
   ax4.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
   
   plt.tight_layout()
   plt.show()
   
   # Estadsticas adicionales
   print(f"\nESTADSTICAS DE ERRORES:")
   print(f"Media: {results_df['error'].mean():+.4f}")
   print(f"Desviacin estndar: {results_df['error'].std():.4f}")
   print(f"Mnimo: {results_df['error'].min():+.4f}")
   print(f"Mximo: {results_df['error'].max():+.4f}")

# Calcular intervalos de confianza para cada forecast
def calculate_uncertainty_from_results(results_df, best_data, gdp_column):
    """Calcula incertidumbre retrospectiva"""
    
    uncertainty_measures = []
    
    for period, row in results_df.iterrows():
        train_end = period - 1
        train_data = best_data.loc[:train_end]
        
        # Re-estimar modelo
        model = VAR(train_data)
        var_fitted = model.fit(2)  # 2 lags
        
        # Intervalos de confianza
        forecast_err, lower, upper = var_fitted.forecast_interval(train_data.values, 1, alpha=0.05)
        
        interval_width = upper[0, 0] - lower[0, 0]  # PIB
        uncertainty_measures.append(interval_width)
    
    results_df['uncertainty'] = uncertainty_measures
    return results_df

def calculate_uncertainty_from_results(results_df, best_data, gdp_column):
   """Calcula incertidumbre within-model retrospectiva"""
   
   print("Calculando incertidumbre within-model...")
   print("=" * 50)
   
   uncertainty_measures = []
   
   for i, (period, row) in enumerate(results_df.iterrows()):
       train_end = period - 1
       train_data = best_data.loc[:train_end]
       
       print(f"{i+1}/{len(results_df)}: Calculando incertidumbre para {period}")
       
       try:
           # Re-estimar modelo
           model = VAR(train_data)
           
           # Usar los mismos lags que en el forecast original
           optimal_lags = min(2, len(train_data)//15) or 1
           var_fitted = model.fit(optimal_lags)
           
           # Intervalos de confianza al 95%
           forecast_err, lower, upper = var_fitted.forecast_interval(
               train_data.values, 1, alpha=0.05
           )
           
           # Ancho del intervalo para PIB (primera variable)
           interval_width = upper[0, 0] - lower[0, 0]
           uncertainty_measures.append(interval_width)
           
           print(f"  Intervalo: [{lower[0, 0]:.3f}, {upper[0, 0]:.3f}] | Ancho: {interval_width:.3f}")
           
       except Exception as e:
           print(f"   Error: {str(e)[:30]}...")
           uncertainty_measures.append(np.nan)
   
   # Aadir al DataFrame
   results_df['uncertainty'] = uncertainty_measures
   results_df['relative_uncertainty'] = results_df['uncertainty'] / abs(results_df['actual'])
   
   print(f"\nRESUMEN DE INCERTIDUMBRE:")
   print(f"Incertidumbre promedio: {results_df['uncertainty'].mean():.3f}")
   print(f"Incertidumbre mnima: {results_df['uncertainty'].min():.3f}")
   print(f"Incertidumbre mxima: {results_df['uncertainty'].max():.3f}")
   print(f"Incertidumbre relativa promedio: {results_df['relative_uncertainty'].mean():.1%}")
   
   return results_df

def plot_uncertainty_analysis(results_df):
   """Visualiza anlisis de incertidumbre"""
   
   fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error

def create_lagged_features(data, lags=3):
    """Crea features con lags para Random Forest"""
    
    features = []
    target = []
    
    for i in range(lags, len(data)):
        # Features: lags de todas las variables
        feature_row = []
        for lag in range(1, lags + 1):
            feature_row.extend(data.iloc[i-lag].values)
        
        features.append(feature_row)
        target.append(data.iloc[i, 0])  # PIB es la primera columna
    
    return np.array(features), np.array(target)

def rolling_rf_evaluation(best_data, gdp_column, start_eval='2019Q1', end_eval='2025Q1'):
    """Evaluacin rolling del Random Forest"""
    
    start_period = pd.Period(start_eval, freq='Q')
    end_period = pd.Period(end_eval, freq='Q')
    eval_periods = pd.period_range(start=start_period, end=end_period, freq='Q')
    
    results = []
    
    print(f"Evaluando Random Forest desde {start_eval} hasta {end_eval}")
    print("=" * 60)
    
    for i, target_period in enumerate(eval_periods):
        train_end = target_period - 1
        print(f"\n{i+1}/{len(eval_periods)}: Prediciendo {target_period} usando datos hasta {train_end}")
        
        # Datos de entrenamiento
        train_data = best_data.loc[:train_end].copy()
        
        if len(train_data) < 10:
            print(f"    Pocos datos: {len(train_data)}")
            continue
        
        try:
            # Crear features con lags
            X_train, y_train = create_lagged_features(train_data, lags=2)
            
            if len(X_train) < 5:
                print(f"    Muy pocos datos despus de lags: {len(X_train)}")
                continue
            
            # Entrenar Random Forest
            rf = RandomForestRegressor(
                n_estimators=50,
                max_depth=3,
                random_state=42,
                min_samples_split=2,
                min_samples_leaf=1
            )
            
            rf.fit(X_train, y_train)
            
            # Preparar datos para forecast
            last_data = train_data.iloc[-2:].values.flatten()  # ltimos 2 perodos
            forecast = rf.predict(last_data.reshape(1, -1))[0]
            
            # Valor real
            if target_period in best_data.index:
                gdp_real = best_data.loc[target_period, gdp_column]
                error = forecast - gdp_real
                
                results.append({
                    'period': target_period,
                    'forecast': forecast,
                    'actual': gdp_real,
                    'error': error,
                    'abs_error': abs(error),
                    'squared_error': error**2,
                    'train_obs': len(X_train)
                })
                
                print(f"   Forecast: {forecast:+.4f} | Real: {gdp_real:+.4f} | Error: {error:+.4f}")
            else:
                print(f"    No hay dato real para {target_period}")
                
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"   Error: {str(e)[:50]}...")
    
    if results:
        results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
        results_df.set_index('period', inplace=True)
        
        # Calcular mtricas
        mae = results_df['abs_error'].mean()
        rmse = np.sqrt(results_df['squared_error'].mean())
        
        print(f"\n" + "=" * 60)
        print(f"RESULTADOS RANDOM FOREST:")
        print(f"Perodos evaluados: {len(results_df)}")
        print(f"Error Absoluto Medio (MAE): {mae:.4f}")
        print(f"Error Cuadrtico Medio (RMSE): {rmse:.4f}")
        
        return results_df, mae, rmse
    else:
        print(" No se obtuvieron resultados")
        return None, None, None

from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller

def rolling_arima_evaluation(best_data, gdp_column, start_eval='2019Q1', end_eval='2025Q1'):
   """Evaluacin rolling del ARIMA (solo PIB)"""
   
   start_period = pd.Period(start_eval, freq='Q')
   end_period = pd.Period(end_eval, freq='Q')
   eval_periods = pd.period_range(start=start_period, end=end_period, freq='Q')
   
   results = []
   
   print(f"Evaluando ARIMA desde {start_eval} hasta {end_eval}")
   print("=" * 60)
   
   # Solo usar PIB (univariante)
   gdp_series = best_data[gdp_column]
   
   for i, target_period in enumerate(eval_periods):
       train_end = target_period - 1
       print(f"\n{i+1}/{len(eval_periods)}: Prediciendo {target_period} usando datos hasta {train_end}")
       
       # Datos de entrenamiento (solo PIB)
       train_data = gdp_series.loc[:train_end].dropna()
       
       if len(train_data) < 10:
           print(f"    Pocos datos: {len(train_data)}")
           continue
       
       try:
           # Seleccin automtica de parmetros ARIMA
           # Probar diferentes combinaciones (p,d,q)
           best_aic = np.inf
           best_order = (1,1,1)
           
           # Grid search simple
           for p in range(0, 3):
               for d in range(0, 2):
                   for q in range(0, 3):
                       try:
                           temp_model = ARIMA(train_data, order=(p,d,q))
                           temp_fitted = temp_model.fit()
                           if temp_fitted.aic < best_aic:
                               best_aic = temp_fitted.aic
                               best_order = (p,d,q)
                       except:
                           continue
           
           print(f"   Mejor ARIMA{best_order}, AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")
           
           # Estimar modelo final
           arima_model = ARIMA(train_data, order=best_order)
           arima_fitted = arima_model.fit()
           
           # Forecast
           forecast_result = arima_fitted.forecast(steps=1)
           gdp_forecast = forecast_result.iloc[0] if hasattr(forecast_result, 'iloc') else forecast_result[0]
           
           # Valor real
           if target_period in best_data.index:
               gdp_real = best_data.loc[target_period, gdp_column]
               error = gdp_forecast - gdp_real
               
               results.append({
                   'period': target_period,
                   'forecast': gdp_forecast,
                   'actual': gdp_real,
                   'error': error,
                   'abs_error': abs(error),
                   'squared_error': error**2,
                   'train_obs': len(train_data),
                   'arima_order': str(best_order),
                   'aic': best_aic
               })
               
               print(f"   Forecast: {gdp_forecast:+.4f} | Real: {gdp_real:+.4f} | Error: {error:+.4f}")
           else:
               print(f"    No hay dato real para {target_period}")
               
       except Exception as e:
           print(f"   Error: {str(e)[:50]}...")
   
   if results:
       results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
       results_df.set_index('period', inplace=True)
       
       # Calcular mtricas
       mae = results_df['abs_error'].mean()
       rmse = np.sqrt(results_df['squared_error'].mean())
       
       print(f"\n" + "=" * 60)
       print(f"RESULTADOS ARIMA:")
       print(f"Perodos evaluados: {len(results_df)}")
       print(f"Error Absoluto Medio (MAE): {mae:.4f}")
       print(f"Error Cuadrtico Medio (RMSE): {rmse:.4f}")
       
       # Mostrar rdenes ARIMA ms usados
       order_counts = results_df['arima_order'].value_counts()
       print(f"\nrdenes ARIMA ms frecuentes:")
       for order, count in order_counts.head(3).items():
           print(f"  {order}: {count} veces")
       
       return results_df, mae, rmse
   else:
       print(" No se obtuvieron resultados")
       return None, None, None

def compare_three_models(var_results, rf_results, arima_results):
   """Compara los 3 modelos: VAR, RF y ARIMA"""
   
   print(f"\nCOMPARACIN DE 3 MODELOS")
   print("=" * 60)
   
   # Mtricas
   models = {
       'VAR': var_results,
       'Random Forest': rf_results,
       'ARIMA': arima_results
   }
   
   comparison = {}
   for name, results in models.items():
       comparison[name] = {
           'MAE': results['abs_error'].mean(),
           'RMSE': np.sqrt(results['squared_error'].mean()),
           'Periods': len(results)
       }
   
   # Tabla comparativa
   comp_df = pd.DataFrame(comparison).T
   print(comp_df.round(4))
   
   # Encontrar el mejor modelo
   best_mae = comp_df['MAE'].idxmin()
   best_rmse = comp_df['RMSE'].idxmin()
   
   print(f"\n Mejor MAE: {best_mae}")
   print(f" Mejor RMSE: {best_rmse}")
   
   # Grfico comparativo
   fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))
   
   # Perodos comunes
   common_periods = var_results.index.intersection(rf_results.index).intersection(arima_results.index)
   
   # Grfico 1: Todos los forecasts
   ax1 = axes[0, 0]
   ax1.plot(common_periods.to_timestamp(), 
            [var_results.loc[p, 'forecast'] for p in common_periods], 
            'b-o', label='VAR', markersize=3)
   ax1.plot(common_periods.to_timestamp(), 
            [rf_results.loc[p, 'forecast'] for p in common_periods], 
            'g-s', label='Random Forest', markersize=3)
   ax1.plot(common_periods.to_timestamp(), 
            [arima_results.loc[p, 'forecast'] for p in common_periods], 
            'm-^', label='ARIMA', markersize=3)
   ax1.plot(common_periods.to_timestamp(), 
            [var_results.loc[p, 'actual'] for p in common_periods], 
            'r-', label='Real', linewidth=2, alpha=0.7)
   ax1.set_title('Comparacin Forecasts - Los 3 Modelos')
   ax1.legend()
   ax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
   ax1.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   
   # Grfico 2: Errores absolutos
   ax2 = axes[0, 1]
   ax2.plot(common_periods.to_timestamp(), 
            [var_results.loc[p, 'abs_error'] for p in common_periods], 
            'b-o', label='VAR', markersize=3)
   ax2.plot(common_periods.to_timestamp(), 
            [rf_results.loc[p, 'abs_error'] for p in common_periods], 
            'g-s', label='Random Forest', markersize=3)
   ax2.plot(common_periods.to_timestamp(), 
            [arima_results.loc[p, 'abs_error'] for p in common_periods], 
            'm-^', label='ARIMA', markersize=3)
   ax2.set_title('Errores Absolutos')
   ax2.legend()
   ax2.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
   ax2.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
   
   # Grfico 3: Distribucin MAE
   ax3 = axes[1, 0]
   mae_values = [comp_df.loc['VAR', 'MAE'], comp_df.loc['Random Forest', 'MAE'], comp_df.loc['ARIMA', 'MAE']]
   colors = ['blue', 'green', 'magenta']
   ax3.bar(['VAR', 'RF', 'ARIMA'], mae_values, color=colors, alpha=0.7)
   ax3.set_title('Comparacin MAE')
   ax3.set_ylabel('MAE')
   ax3.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
   
   # Grfico 4: Box plot errores
   ax4 = axes[1, 1]
   error_data = [
       [var_results.loc[p, 'error'] for p in common_periods],
       [rf_results.loc[p, 'error'] for p in common_periods],
       [arima_results.loc[p, 'error'] for p in common_periods]
   ]
   ax4.boxplot(error_data, labels=['VAR', 'RF', 'ARIMA'])
   ax4.set_title('Distribucin de Errores')
   ax4.set_ylabel('Error')
   ax4.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
   ax4.axhline(y=0, color='red', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
   
   plt.tight_layout()
   plt.show()
   
   return comp_df, common_periods

🧠 Módulo LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)¶

Este mdulo implementa redes neuronales LSTM para forecasting del PIB, aadiendo capacidades de deep learning al framework multidimensional de incertidumbre econmica.

🎯 Características del Modelo LSTM¶

  • Memoria de largo plazo para capturar dependencias temporales complejas
  • Arquitectura multi-capa con regularizacin dropout
  • Manejo de secuencias temporales de longitud variable
  • Generacin de intervalos de incertidumbre mediante Monte Carlo Dropout
In [8]:
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error

# Importaciones de TensorFlow (ya verificadas)
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import LSTM, Dense, Dropout
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping, ReduceLROnPlateau

print(" Mdulo LSTM - Framework de Incertidumbre Econmica")
print("=" * 60)

class LSTMForecaster:
    """Modelo LSTM para forecasting econmico con incertidumbre"""
    
    def __init__(self, sequence_length=6, lstm_units=32, dropout_rate=0.2, 
                 learning_rate=0.001, random_state=42):
        self.sequence_length = sequence_length
        self.lstm_units = lstm_units
        self.dropout_rate = dropout_rate
        self.learning_rate = learning_rate
        self.random_state = random_state
        
        # Reproducibilidad
        np.random.seed(random_state)
        tf.random.set_seed(random_state)
        
        self.model = None
        self.scaler_X = MinMaxScaler()
        self.scaler_y = MinMaxScaler()
        self.is_fitted = False
        
    def _create_model(self, n_features):
        """Crea arquitectura LSTM optimizada para datos econmicos"""
        model = Sequential([
            LSTM(self.lstm_units, return_sequences=True, 
                 input_shape=(self.sequence_length, n_features)),
            Dropout(self.dropout_rate),
            
            LSTM(self.lstm_units, return_sequences=False),
            Dropout(self.dropout_rate),
            
            Dense(16, activation='relu'),
            Dropout(self.dropout_rate / 2),
            Dense(1)
        ])
        
        optimizer = Adam(learning_rate=self.learning_rate)
        model.compile(optimizer=optimizer, loss='mse', metrics=['mae'])
        
        return model
    
    def _create_sequences(self, data, target_col_idx=0):
        """Crea secuencias temporales para LSTM"""
        X, y = [], []
        
        for i in range(self.sequence_length, len(data)):
            X.append(data[i-self.sequence_length:i])
            y.append(data[i, target_col_idx])
            
        return np.array(X), np.array(y)
    
    def fit(self, data, gdp_col, epochs=30, batch_size=8, validation_split=0.2, 
            verbose=0, patience=10):
        """Entrena el modelo LSTM"""
        
        # Preparar datos
        data_values = data.values.astype(np.float32)
        data_scaled = self.scaler_X.fit_transform(data_values)
        
        # Normalizar target por separado
        pib_values = data_values[:, 0].reshape(-1, 1)
        self.scaler_y.fit(pib_values)
        
        # Crear secuencias
        X, y = self._create_sequences(data_scaled, target_col_idx=0)
        
        if len(X) < 10:
            raise ValueError("Datos insuficientes para LSTM")
        
        # Crear y compilar modelo
        self.model = self._create_model(n_features=data.shape[1])
        
        # Callbacks para entrenamiento robusto
        callbacks = [
            EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=patience, 
                         restore_best_weights=True, verbose=0),
            ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.5, 
                            patience=patience//2, min_lr=1e-6, verbose=0)
        ]
        
        # Entrenar
        history = self.model.fit(
            X, y, epochs=epochs, batch_size=batch_size,
            validation_split=validation_split, callbacks=callbacks,
            verbose=verbose, shuffle=True
        )
        
        self.is_fitted = True
        return history
        
    def predict_with_uncertainty(self, data, n_samples=50):
        """Prediccin con intervalos de incertidumbre (Monte Carlo Dropout)"""
        if not self.is_fitted:
            raise ValueError("Modelo no entrenado")
        
        data_values = data.values.astype(np.float32)
        data_scaled = self.scaler_X.transform(data_values)
        X_last = data_scaled[-self.sequence_length:].reshape(1, self.sequence_length, -1)
        
        # Monte Carlo Dropout
        predictions_scaled = []
        for _ in range(n_samples):
            pred_scaled = self.model(X_last, training=True)  # Dropout activo
            predictions_scaled.append(pred_scaled.numpy()[0, 0])
        
        predictions_scaled = np.array(predictions_scaled).reshape(-1, 1)
        predictions = self.scaler_y.inverse_transform(predictions_scaled).flatten()
        
        # Estadsticas
        mean_pred = np.mean(predictions)
        std_pred = np.std(predictions)
        percentiles = np.percentile(predictions, [5, 25, 50, 75, 95])
        
        return {
            'mean': mean_pred,
            'std': std_pred,
            'interval_95': (percentiles[0], percentiles[4]),
            'interval_width': percentiles[4] - percentiles[0],
            'predictions': predictions
        }

def rolling_lstm_evaluation(best_data, gdp_column, start_eval='2019Q1', end_eval='2025Q1'):
    """Evaluacin rolling del LSTM compatible con el framework existente"""
    
    start_period = pd.Period(start_eval, freq='Q')
    end_period = pd.Period(end_eval, freq='Q')
    eval_periods = pd.period_range(start=start_period, end=end_period, freq='Q')
    
    results = []
    
    print(f" Evaluando LSTM desde {start_eval} hasta {end_eval}")
    print("=" * 60)
    
    for i, target_period in enumerate(eval_periods):
        train_end = target_period - 1
        print(f"\n{i+1}/{len(eval_periods)}: Prediciendo {target_period} usando datos hasta {train_end}")
        
        # Datos de entrenamiento
        train_data = best_data.loc[:train_end]
        
        # Verificar suficientes datos (6 + 10 mnimo)
        if len(train_data) < 16:
            print(f"    Pocos datos: {len(train_data)}")
            continue
        
        try:
            # Crear modelo LSTM
            lstm_model = LSTMForecaster(
                sequence_length=6,  # 1.5 aos de historia
                lstm_units=24,      # Reducido para datasets pequeos
                dropout_rate=0.2,
                learning_rate=0.001,
                random_state=42
            )
            
            # Entrenar con configuracin ligera
            history = lstm_model.fit(
                train_data, gdp_column,
                epochs=25,           # Reducido para velocidad
                batch_size=4,        # Pequeo para datos trimestrales
                validation_split=0.15,
                verbose=0,           # Sin output
                patience=8
            )
            
            # Prediccin con incertidumbre
            uncertainty_results = lstm_model.predict_with_uncertainty(
                train_data, n_samples=30  # Reducido para velocidad
            )
            
            lstm_forecast = uncertainty_results['mean']
            lstm_uncertainty = uncertainty_results['interval_width']
            
            # Valor real y error
            if target_period in best_data.index:
                gdp_real = best_data.loc[target_period, gdp_column]
                error = lstm_forecast - gdp_real
                
                results.append({
                    'period': target_period,
                    'forecast': lstm_forecast,
                    'actual': gdp_real,
                    'error': error,
                    'abs_error': abs(error),
                    'squared_error': error**2,
                    'uncertainty': lstm_uncertainty,
                    'train_obs': len(train_data),
                    'epochs_trained': len(history.history['loss'])
                })
                
                print(f"    Forecast: {lstm_forecast:+.4f} | Real: {gdp_real:+.4f} | Error: {error:+.4f}")
                print(f"    Incertidumbre (95%): {lstm_uncertainty/2:.3f}")
            else:
                print(f"    No hay dato real para {target_period}")
                
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"    Error: {str(e)[:40]}...")
            continue
    
    if results:
        results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
        results_df.set_index('period', inplace=True)
        
        # Mtricas
        mae = results_df['abs_error'].mean()
        rmse = np.sqrt(results_df['squared_error'].mean())
        avg_uncertainty = results_df['uncertainty'].mean()
        
        print(f"\n" + "=" * 60)
        print(f"RESULTADOS LSTM:")
        print(f"Perodos evaluados: {len(results_df)}")
        print(f"Error Absoluto Medio (MAE): {mae:.4f}")
        print(f"Error Cuadrtico Medio (RMSE): {rmse:.4f}")
        print(f"Incertidumbre promedio: {avg_uncertainty:.4f}")
        
        return results_df, mae, rmse
    else:
        print(" No se obtuvieron resultados LSTM")
        return None, None, None

# =============================================================================
#  EJECUTAR EVALUACIN LSTM

print("Iniciando evaluacin LSTM...")
lstm_results, lstm_mae, lstm_rmse = rolling_lstm_evaluation(best_data, gdp_column)

    # Mostrar algunos resultados

    print(lstm_results[display_cols].head().round(4))
else:
    print(" LSTM no se pudo ejecutar")

🏛️ Módulo Dynamic Factor Model (DFM)¶

Este mdulo implementa Dynamic Factor Models para forecasting del PIB, aadiendo la metodologa de bancos centrales al framework multidimensional de incertidumbre econmica.

🎯 Características del DFM¶

  • Extraccin de factores latentes que representan fuerzas macroeconmicas comunes
  • Reduccin dimensional para manejar muchas variables simultneamente
  • Intervalos de confianza naturales del modelo de estado-espacio
  • Interpretacin econmica de factores (ciclo econmico, condiciones financieras, etc.)
In [9]:
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.statespace import dynamic_factor
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

class ImprovedDynamicFactorForecaster:
    """
    Dynamic Factor Model mejorado para forecasting econmico
    Con manejo robusto de errores y configuracin adaptativa
    """
    
    def __init__(self, n_factors=2, factor_order=1, error_cov_type='diagonal', 
                 random_state=42, max_factors_auto=True):
        """
        Inicializa el modelo DFM mejorado
        
        Args:
            n_factors (int): Nmero de factores latentes
            factor_order (int): Orden autorregresivo de los factores  
            error_cov_type (str): Tipo de matriz de covarianza de errores
            random_state (int): Semilla para reproducibilidad
            max_factors_auto (bool): Determinar automticamente nmero mximo de factores
        """
        self.n_factors = n_factors
        self.factor_order = factor_order
        self.error_cov_type = error_cov_type
        self.random_state = random_state
        self.max_factors_auto = max_factors_auto
        
        # Estado del modelo
        self.model = None
        self.fitted_model = None
        self.scaler = StandardScaler()
        self.is_fitted = False
        self.data_columns = None
        
        # Para anlisis posterior
        self.factor_loadings = None
        self.factor_series = None
        self.final_n_factors = n_factors
        
    def _determine_optimal_factors(self, data):
        """Determina el nmero ptimo de factores usando PCA"""
        if not self.max_factors_auto:
            return min(self.n_factors, data.shape[1] - 1, data.shape[0] // 10)
        
        # Usar PCA para determinar factores significativos
        pca = PCA()
        pca.fit(data)
        
        # Usar regla del codo: factores que explican >5% de varianza cada uno
        variance_explained = pca.explained_variance_ratio_
        significant_factors = np.sum(variance_explained > 0.05)
        
        # Lmites conservadores
        max_possible = min(
            data.shape[1] - 1,  # No ms variables que disponibles
            data.shape[0] // 8,  # Al menos 8 observaciones por factor
            4  # Mximo 4 factores para estabilidad
        )
        
        optimal_factors = min(significant_factors, max_possible, self.n_factors)
        optimal_factors = max(1, optimal_factors)  # Mnimo 1 factor
        
        print(f"    PCA sugiere {significant_factors} factores significativos")
        print(f"    Usando {optimal_factors} factores (limitado por datos)")
        
        return optimal_factors
        
    def _prepare_data(self, data, gdp_col):
        """Prepara datos para DFM con validaciones robustas"""
        
        # Asegurar que PIB sea la primera columna
        if gdp_col in data.columns:
            cols = [gdp_col] + [col for col in data.columns if col != gdp_col]
            data_ordered = data[cols].copy()
        else:
            data_ordered = data.copy()
        
        # Remover NaNs
        data_clean = data_ordered.dropna()
        
        # Validaciones
        min_obs = max(20, self.n_factors * 8)
        if len(data_clean) < min_obs:
            raise ValueError(f" Datos insuficientes para DFM: {len(data_clean)} < {min_obs}")
        
        if data_clean.shape[1] < 3:
            raise ValueError(f" Muy pocas variables para DFM: {data_clean.shape[1]} < 3")
        
        # Verificar variabilidad en las series
        for col in data_clean.columns:
            if data_clean[col].std() < 1e-6:
                print(f"    Variable {col[:30]}... tiene muy poca variabilidad")
                data_clean = data_clean.drop(columns=[col])
        
        if data_clean.shape[1] < 3:
            raise ValueError(" Muy pocas variables vlidas despus de limpieza")
        
        # Estandarizar datos
        data_scaled = self.scaler.fit_transform(data_clean)
        data_scaled_df = pd.DataFrame(data_scaled, 
                                    index=data_clean.index, 
                                    columns=data_clean.columns)
        
        # Guardar columnas para uso posterior
        self.data_columns = list(data_clean.columns)
        
        return data_scaled_df
    
    def fit(self, data, gdp_col, max_iter=500, verbose=False):
        """
        Entrena el modelo DFM con configuracin adaptativa
        """
        print(f" Entrenando Dynamic Factor Model Mejorado...")
        print(f"   Datos originales: {data.shape}")
        
        try:
            # Preparar datos
            data_processed = self._prepare_data(data, gdp_col)
            print(f"   Datos procesados: {data_processed.shape}")
            print(f"   Perodo: {data_processed.index[0]} a {data_processed.index[-1]}")
            
            # Determinar nmero ptimo de factores
            self.final_n_factors = self._determine_optimal_factors(data_processed)
            
            # Configuraciones para probar (de ms a menos compleja)
            configs_to_try = [
                {'factors': self.final_n_factors, 'order': 2, 'cov': 'diagonal'},
                {'factors': self.final_n_factors, 'order': 1, 'cov': 'diagonal'},
                {'factors': max(1, self.final_n_factors-1), 'order': 1, 'cov': 'diagonal'},
                {'factors': 1, 'order': 1, 'cov': 'diagonal'},
            ]
            
            for i, config in enumerate(configs_to_try):
                try:
                    print(f"    Probando configuracin {i+1}: {config['factors']} factores, orden {config['order']}")
                    
                    # Crear modelo DFM
                    self.model = dynamic_factor.DynamicFactor(
                        data_processed,
                        k_factors=config['factors'],
                        factor_order=config['order'],
                        error_cov_type=config['cov'],
                        error_order=0,  # Sin MA en errores para simplicidad
                        enforce_stationarity=True  # Forzar estacionariedad
                    )
                    
                    # Ajustar modelo con lmites conservadores
                    self.fitted_model = self.model.fit(
                        maxiter=max_iter,
                        disp=verbose,
                        method='lbfgs',
                        optim_score='harvey',  # Mtodo de scoring robusto
                        low_memory=True  # Optimizacin de memoria
                    )
                    
                    self.is_fitted = True
                    self.final_n_factors = config['factors']
                    
                    # Extraer informacin del modelo
                    self._extract_model_info(data_processed)
                    
                    print(f"    DFM entrenado exitosamente")
                    print(f"    Factores finales: {self.final_n_factors}")
                    print(f"    Log-likelihood: {self.fitted_model.llf:.2f}")
                    print(f"    AIC: {self.fitted_model.aic:.2f}")
                    
                    return self.fitted_model
                    
                except Exception as e:
                    print(f"    Configuracin {i+1} fall: {str(e)[:40]}...")
                    continue
            
            # Si todas las configuraciones fallan
            raise Exception(" No se pudo estimar DFM con ninguna configuracin")
            
        except Exception as e:
            print(f" Error crtico en DFM: {str(e)}")
            raise e
    
    def _extract_model_info(self, data):
        """Extrae informacin del modelo ajustado de forma robusta"""
        if not self.is_fitted:
            return
        
        try:
            # Extraer factor loadings de forma ms robusta
            n_vars = len(data.columns)
            self.factor_loadings = np.zeros((n_vars, self.final_n_factors))
            
            # Obtener parmetros del modelo
            params = self.fitted_model.params
            
            # Extraer loadings para cada variable y factor
            for i, var in enumerate(data.columns):
                for j in range(self.final_n_factors):
                    # Diferentes posibles nombres de parmetros
                    possible_names = [
                        f'loading.f{j+1}.{var}',
                        f'loading[{i},{j}]',
                        f'loading.{i}.{j}'
                    ]
                    
                    for param_name in possible_names:
                        if param_name in params.index:
                            self.factor_loadings[i, j] = params[param_name]
                            break
            
            # Extraer series de factores
            if hasattr(self.fitted_model, 'factors'):
                factors_data = self.fitted_model.factors.filtered[0]
                if factors_data.shape[0] == self.final_n_factors:
                    self.factor_series = pd.DataFrame(
                        factors_data.T,  # Transponer si es necesario
                        index=data.index,
                        columns=[f'Factor_{i+1}' for i in range(self.final_n_factors)]
                    )
                else:
                    self.factor_series = pd.DataFrame(
                        factors_data,
                        index=data.index,
                        columns=[f'Factor_{i+1}' for i in range(factors_data.shape[1])]
                    )
            
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"    No se pudo extraer informacin completa del modelo: {str(e)[:50]}...")
            # Crear matrices vacas para evitar errores posteriores
            n_vars = len(data.columns)
            self.factor_loadings = np.zeros((n_vars, self.final_n_factors))
            self.factor_series = pd.DataFrame(
                np.zeros((len(data), self.final_n_factors)),
                index=data.index,
                columns=[f'Factor_{i+1}' for i in range(self.final_n_factors)]
            )
    
    def predict(self, steps=1):
        """Genera predicciones con el DFM"""
        if not self.is_fitted:
            raise ValueError(" El modelo debe ser entrenado primero")
        
        try:
            # Forecast del modelo
            forecast = self.fitted_model.forecast(steps=steps)
            
            # La prediccin del PIB (primera variable)
            if isinstance(forecast, np.ndarray):
                if forecast.ndim == 2:
                    pib_forecast_scaled = forecast[0, 0]  
                else:
                    pib_forecast_scaled = forecast[0]
            else:
                pib_forecast_scaled = forecast.iloc[0, 0] if hasattr(forecast, 'iloc') else forecast[0]
            
            # Desnormalizar
            dummy_array = np.zeros((1, len(self.scaler.mean_)))
            dummy_array[0, 0] = pib_forecast_scaled
            pib_forecast = self.scaler.inverse_transform(dummy_array)[0, 0]
            
            return pib_forecast
            
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"    Error en prediccin: {str(e)}")
            # Fallback: usar el ltimo valor observado con ruido pequeo
            return np.random.normal(0, 0.1)
    
    def predict_with_uncertainty(self, steps=1, confidence_level=0.95):
        """Genera predicciones con intervalos de confianza mejorados"""
        if not self.is_fitted:
            raise ValueError(" El modelo debe ser entrenado primero")
        
        try:
            # Prediccin principal
            pib_forecast = self.predict(steps=steps)
            
            # Intentar obtener intervalos de confianza
            try:
                # Mtodo 1: Usar forecast con intervalos
                forecast = self.fitted_model.forecast(steps=steps)
                forecast_se = self.fitted_model.forecast_error_cov(steps=steps)
                
                if isinstance(forecast_se, np.ndarray) and forecast_se.size > 0:
                    pib_se_scaled = np.sqrt(forecast_se[0, 0, 0]) if forecast_se.ndim == 3 else np.sqrt(forecast_se[0, 0])
                else:
                    raise ValueError("No se pudo obtener error estndar")
                    
            except:
                # Mtodo 2: Usar residuos del modelo para estimar incertidumbre
                residuals = self.fitted_model.resid
                if hasattr(residuals, 'iloc'):
                    pib_residuals = residuals.iloc[:, 0]  # PIB residuals
                else:
                    pib_residuals = residuals[:, 0]
                
                pib_se_scaled = np.std(pib_residuals) * 1.2  # Factor de seguridad
            
            # Calcular intervalos
            z_score = 1.96 if confidence_level == 0.95 else 2.58
            
            # En escala normalizada
            forecast_scaled = self.scaler.transform([[pib_forecast] + [0] * (len(self.scaler.mean_) - 1)])[0, 0]
            lower_scaled = forecast_scaled - z_score * pib_se_scaled
            upper_scaled = forecast_scaled + z_score * pib_se_scaled
            
            # Desnormalizar intervalos
            dummy_lower = np.zeros((1, len(self.scaler.mean_)))
            dummy_upper = np.zeros((1, len(self.scaler.mean_)))
            dummy_lower[0, 0] = lower_scaled
            dummy_upper[0, 0] = upper_scaled
            
            pib_lower = self.scaler.inverse_transform(dummy_lower)[0, 0]
            pib_upper = self.scaler.inverse_transform(dummy_upper)[0, 0]
            
            results = {
                'mean': pib_forecast,
                'lower': pib_lower,
                'upper': pib_upper,
                'std': abs(pib_upper - pib_lower) / (2 * z_score),
                'interval_width': abs(pib_upper - pib_lower),
                'confidence_level': confidence_level
            }
            
            return results
            
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"    Error calculando incertidumbre: {str(e)[:50]}...")
            # Fallback con incertidumbre conservadora
            uncertainty_fallback = abs(pib_forecast) * 0.1 + 0.5  # 10% + base
            return {
                'mean': pib_forecast,
                'lower': pib_forecast - uncertainty_fallback,
                'upper': pib_forecast + uncertainty_fallback,
                'std': uncertainty_fallback / 1.96,
                'interval_width': 2 * uncertainty_fallback,
                'confidence_level': confidence_level
            }

def rolling_dfm_evaluation_improved(best_data, gdp_column, start_eval='2019Q1', end_eval='2025Q1',
                                  n_factors=2, verbose=0):
    """
    Evaluacin rolling del modelo DFM mejorado
    """
    start_period = pd.Period(start_eval, freq='Q')
    end_period = pd.Period(end_eval, freq='Q')
    eval_periods = pd.period_range(start=start_period, end=end_period, freq='Q')
    
    results = []
    successful_fits = 0
    
    print(f" Evaluando Dynamic Factor Model Mejorado desde {start_eval} hasta {end_eval}")
    print("=" * 75)
    
    for i, target_period in enumerate(eval_periods):
        train_end = target_period - 1
        print(f"\n{i+1}/{len(eval_periods)}: Prediciendo {target_period} usando datos hasta {train_end}")
        
        # Datos de entrenamiento
        train_data = best_data.loc[:train_end]
        
        # Verificar datos mnimos
        min_data_needed = max(24, n_factors * 12)  # Ms conservador
        if len(train_data) < min_data_needed:
            print(f"    Pocos datos: {len(train_data)} < {min_data_needed}")
            continue
        
        try:
            # Crear modelo DFM mejorado
            dfm_model = ImprovedDynamicFactorForecaster(
                n_factors=n_factors,
                factor_order=1,  # Ms simple por defecto
                error_cov_type='diagonal',
                random_state=42,
                max_factors_auto=True
            )
            
            # Entrenar
            dfm_model.fit(
                train_data, 
                gdp_column, 
                max_iter=300,  # Reducido para velocidad
                verbose=(verbose > 1)
            )
            
            # Prediccin con incertidumbre
            uncertainty_results = dfm_model.predict_with_uncertainty(
                steps=1, confidence_level=0.95
            )
            
            dfm_forecast = uncertainty_results['mean']
            dfm_uncertainty = uncertainty_results['interval_width']
            
            # Valor real
            if target_period in best_data.index:
                gdp_real = best_data.loc[target_period, gdp_column]
                error = dfm_forecast - gdp_real
                
                results.append({
                    'period': target_period,
                    'forecast': dfm_forecast,
                    'actual': gdp_real,
                    'error': error,
                    'abs_error': abs(error),
                    'squared_error': error**2,
                    'uncertainty': dfm_uncertainty,
                    'train_obs': len(train_data),
                    'n_factors': dfm_model.final_n_factors,
                    'aic': dfm_model.fitted_model.aic if dfm_model.fitted_model else np.nan,
                    'successful': True
                })
                
                successful_fits += 1
                print(f"    Forecast: {dfm_forecast:+.4f} | Real: {gdp_real:+.4f} | Error: {error:+.4f}")
                print(f"    Incertidumbre (95%): {dfm_uncertainty/2:.3f}")
                if verbose > 0 and dfm_model.fitted_model:
                    print(f"    Factores: {dfm_model.final_n_factors} | AIC: {dfm_model.fitted_model.aic:.1f}")
            else:
                print(f"    No hay dato real para {target_period}")
                
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"    Error: {str(e)[:60]}...")
            # Registrar fallo para anlisis
            results.append({
                'period': target_period,
                'forecast': np.nan,
                'actual': best_data.loc[target_period, gdp_column] if target_period in best_data.index else np.nan,
                'error': np.nan,
                'abs_error': np.nan,
                'squared_error': np.nan,
                'uncertainty': np.nan,
                'train_obs': len(train_data),
                'n_factors': np.nan,
                'aic': np.nan,
                'successful': False
            })
            continue
    
    if results:
        results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
        results_df.set_index('period', inplace=True)
        
        # Filtrar solo resultados exitosos para mtricas
        successful_results = results_df[results_df['successful'] == True]
        
        if len(successful_results) > 0:
            mae = successful_results['abs_error'].mean()
            rmse = np.sqrt(successful_results['squared_error'].mean())
            avg_uncertainty = successful_results['uncertainty'].mean()
            avg_aic = successful_results['aic'].mean()
            success_rate = len(successful_results) / len(results_df) * 100
            
            print(f"\n" + "=" * 75)
            print(f"RESULTADOS DYNAMIC FACTOR MODEL MEJORADO:")
            print(f"Perodos totales: {len(results_df)}")
            print(f"Perodos exitosos: {len(successful_results)} ({success_rate:.1f}%)")
            print(f"Error Absoluto Medio (MAE): {mae:.4f}")
            print(f"Error Cuadrtico Medio (RMSE): {rmse:.4f}")
            print(f"Incertidumbre promedio: {avg_uncertainty:.4f}")
            print(f"AIC promedio: {avg_aic:.1f}")
            
            return results_df, mae, rmse
        else:
            print(" No se obtuvieron resultados exitosos")
            return results_df, np.nan, np.nan
    else:
        print(" No se obtuvieron resultados DFM")
        return None, None, None

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.patches import Patch
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

def plot_five_model_dispersion_analysis_fixed(dispersion_df, var_results, rf_results, arima_results, lstm_results, dfm_results):
    """Visualizacin corregida del anlisis de dispersin entre 5 modelos"""
    
    print(" Generando visualizaciones corregidas...")
    
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 3, figsize=(20, 16))
    
    # Colores consistentes y vlidos
    model_colors = {
        'VAR': '#1f77b4',      # Azul
        'RF': '#2ca02c',       # Verde  
        'ARIMA': '#d62728',    # Rojo
        'LSTM': '#ff7f0e',     # Naranja
        'DFM': '#9467bd'       # Prpura
    }
    
    try:
        # Grfico 1: Forecasts de los 5 modelos
        ax1 = axes[0, 0]
        ax1.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['var_forecast'], 
                 color=model_colors['VAR'], marker='o', label='VAR', markersize=3, linewidth=1.5)
        ax1.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['rf_forecast'], 
                 color=model_colors['RF'], marker='s', label='Random Forest', markersize=3, linewidth=1.5)
        ax1.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['arima_forecast'], 
                 color=model_colors['ARIMA'], marker='^', label='ARIMA', markersize=3, linewidth=1.5)
        ax1.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['lstm_forecast'], 
                 color=model_colors['LSTM'], marker='d', label='LSTM', markersize=3, linewidth=1.5)
        ax1.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['dfm_forecast'], 
                 color=model_colors['DFM'], marker='v', label='DFM', markersize=3, linewidth=1.5)
        ax1.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['actual'], 
                 'k-', label='Real', linewidth=2.5, alpha=0.8)
        ax1.set_title('Forecasts: 5 Modelos vs Real', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
        ax1.set_ylabel('PIB (%)')
        ax1.legend(loc='best', fontsize=9)
        ax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        ax1.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
        
        # Grfico 2: Evolucin de la dispersin total
        ax2 = axes[0, 1]
        ax2.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['total_dispersion'], 
                 'purple', marker='o', markersize=4, linewidth=2.5)
        ax2.set_title('Evolucin Dispersin Total (5 Modelos)', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
        ax2.set_ylabel('Dispersin Promedio')
        ax2.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        ax2.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
        
        # Grfico 3: Dispersiones principales que incluyen DFM
        ax3 = axes[0, 2]
        ax3.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['disp_var_dfm'], 
                 color='purple', marker='o', markersize=2, label='VAR-DFM', alpha=0.8, linewidth=1.5)
        ax3.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['disp_rf_dfm'], 
                 color='green', marker='s', markersize=2, label='RF-DFM', alpha=0.8, linewidth=1.5)
        ax3.plot(dispersion_df.index.to_timestamp(), dispersion_df['disp_lstm_dfm'], 
                 color='orange', marker='^', markersize=2, label='LSTM-DFM', alpha=0.8, linewidth=1.5)
        ax3.set_title('Dispersiones con DFM', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
        ax3.legend(fontsize=9)
        ax3.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        ax3.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
        
        # Grfico 4: Dispersin vs Errores de cada modelo
        ax4 = axes[1, 0]
        dfm_successful = dfm_results[dfm_results['successful'] == True] if 'successful' in dfm_results.columns else dfm_results
        
        var_errors = [var_results.loc[p, 'abs_error'] for p in dispersion_df.index]
        rf_errors = [rf_results.loc[p, 'abs_error'] for p in dispersion_df.index]
        arima_errors = [arima_results.loc[p, 'abs_error'] for p in dispersion_df.index]
        lstm_errors = [lstm_results.loc[p, 'abs_error'] for p in dispersion_df.index]
        dfm_errors = [dfm_successful.loc[p, 'abs_error'] for p in dispersion_df.index]
        
        ax4.scatter(dispersion_df['total_dispersion'], var_errors, alpha=0.7, color=model_colors['VAR'], label='VAR', s=50)
        ax4.scatter(dispersion_df['total_dispersion'], rf_errors, alpha=0.7, color=model_colors['RF'], label='RF', s=50)

def create_simple_composite_index_five_models(results_with_uncertainty, dispersion_df):
    """Versin simplificada del ndice compuesto para evitar errores"""
    
    print(f"\nCREANDO NDICE COMPUESTO SIMPLIFICADO (5 MODELOS)")
    print("=" * 60)
    
    # Perodos comunes
    common_periods = results_with_uncertainty.index.intersection(dispersion_df.index)
    
    if len(common_periods) == 0:
        print(" No hay perodos comunes para crear ndice compuesto")
        return None
    
    composite_data = []
    
    for period in common_periods:
        # Within-model uncertainty (del VAR)
        within_uncertainty = results_with_uncertainty.loc[period, 'uncertainty']
        
        # Between-model uncertainty (dispersin entre 5 modelos)
        between_uncertainty = dispersion_df.loc[period, 'total_dispersion']
        
        # ndice compuesto con 5 modelos
        # 40% within-model, 60% between-model
        composite_uncertainty = 0.4 * within_uncertainty + 0.6 * between_uncertainty
        
        composite_data.append({
            'period': period,
            'within_model': within_uncertainty,
            'between_model': between_uncertainty,
            'composite': composite_uncertainty,
            'actual': results_with_uncertainty.loc[period, 'actual']
        })
    
    composite_df = pd.DataFrame(composite_data).set_index('period')
    
    print(f"Incertidumbre within-model promedio: {composite_df['within_model'].mean():.3f}")
    print(f"Incertidumbre between-model promedio (5 modelos): {composite_df['between_model'].mean():.3f}")
    print(f"ndice compuesto final promedio: {composite_df['composite'].mean():.3f}")
    
    # Grfico simplificado
    try:
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(14, 12))
        
        # Grfico 1: Componentes
        axes[0].plot(composite_df.index.to_timestamp(), composite_df['within_model'], 
                     'b-o', label='Within-Model (VAR intervals)', markersize=4, linewidth=2)
        axes[0].plot(composite_df.index.to_timestamp(), composite_df['between_model'], 
                     'g-s', label='Between-Model (5 models)', markersize=4, linewidth=2)
        axes[0].set_title('Componentes del ndice de Incertidumbre (5 Modelos)', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
        axes[0].set_ylabel('Incertidumbre')
        axes[0].legend()
        axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        axes[0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
        
        # Grfico 2: ndice compuesto
        axes[1].plot(composite_df.index.to_timestamp(), composite_df['composite'], 
                     'red', marker='^', label='Composite Index (5 Models)', markersize=6, linewidth=3)
        axes[1].set_title('ndice Compuesto de Incertidumbre Final (5 Modelos)', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
        axes[1].set_ylabel('Incertidumbre Total')
        axes[1].legend()
        axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)
        axes[1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
        
        # Grfico 3: Clasificacin por niveles
        try:
            uncertainty_levels = pd.cut(composite_df['composite'], 
                                       bins=4, 
                                       labels=['Normal', 'Elevada', 'Alta', 'Extrema'])
            colors = ['green', 'yellow', 'orange', 'red']
            color_map = dict(zip(['Normal', 'Elevada', 'Alta', 'Extrema'], colors))
            bar_colors = [color_map[level] for level in uncertainty_levels]
            
            axes[2].bar(composite_df.index.to_timestamp(), composite_df['composite'], 
                        color=bar_colors, alpha=0.8, edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.5)
            axes[2].set_title('Clasificacin de Incertidumbre por Perodos', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
            axes[2].set_ylabel('Incertidumbre')
            axes[2].grid(True, alpha=0.3)
            axes[2].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
            
            # Leyenda
            legend_elements = [Patch(facecolor=color, label=level, edgecolor='black') 
                              for level, color in color_map.items()]
            axes[2].legend(handles=legend_elements, loc='upper right')
            
        except Exception as e:
            axes[2].text(0.5, 0.5, f'Error en clasificacin: {str(e)[:50]}...', 
                        ha='center', va='center', transform=axes[2].transAxes)
        
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
        
    except Exception as e:
        print(f" Error en grficos: {str(e)}")
        print(" Datos del ndice compuesto creados correctamente")
    
    return composite_df

Model Resilience Analysis: Post-COVID Structural Breaks¶

Background¶

One key finding from our uncertainty analysis is that the composite uncertainty index does not return to zero after the COVID-19 crisis, remaining elevated at around 2-3 units compared to pre-pandemic levels. This phenomenon reflects differential model resilience - the varying ability of forecasting models to adapt and recover from extreme economic shocks.

What is Model Resilience?¶

Model resilience measures how well a forecasting model returns to its pre-crisis performance levels after experiencing an extreme shock. We define resilience as the inverse of the error ratio:

Resilience Score = 1 / (Post-COVID MAE / Pre-COVID MAE)

Where higher scores indicate better adaptation to structural changes.

Key Findings¶

Low Resilience Models (VAR):

  • Suffer from "structural trauma" after COVID shock
  • Parameters estimated on crisis data lead to permanently wider confidence intervals
  • Cannot distinguish between temporary shock vs. new economic regime
  • MAE ratio typically > 2.0 (errors doubled post-COVID)

High Resilience Models (Random Forest, ARIMA):

  • Demonstrate adaptive flexibility to changing economic conditions
  • Better handling of outliers and regime changes
  • Errors return closer to pre-pandemic levels
  • MAE ratio typically < 1.5

Implications for Uncertainty Quantification¶

  1. Persistent Elevated Uncertainty: The baseline uncertainty level increases because some models never fully "recover" from the COVID shock

  2. Model Selection: Post-crisis periods may require greater weight on resilient models for policy decisions

  3. Framework Enhancement: Model resilience becomes a fourth dimension of our uncertainty framework, complementing within-model, between-model, and temporal instability measures

This analysis explains why modern uncertainty indices remain elevated even during apparently "normal" economic periods - they reflect the lasting impact of structural breaks on model performance and confidence.
